   * @param _spender address The address which will spend the funds.

allowance(address,address).notice: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Approve the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

balanceOf(address).notice: Gets the balance of the specified address.

balanceOfAvailable(address).notice: Gets available balance of the specified address

balanceOfFrozen(address).notice: Gets the frozen balance of the specified address

burn(uint256).notice: Destroy tokens Remove `_amount` tokens from the system irreversibly

burnFrom(address,uint256).notice: Destroy tokens from other account Remove `_amount` tokens from the system irreversibly on behalf of `_from`.

decreaseApproval(address,uint256).notice: Decrease the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To decrement allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

depositEtherToContract().notice: deposit ether to account of contract

freezeAccount(address,bool).notice: Frozen account of the specified address

freezeFunds(uint256).notice: Froze amount of money of the own address

freezeFundsFrom(address,bool,uint256).notice: Froze amount of money of the specified address

frozenAccount(address).notice: Gets frozen status of the specified address

increaseApproval(address,uint256).notice: Increase the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfer token for a specified address

transferEtherToOwner(uint256).notice: transfer Ether balance to owner from account of contract

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer tokens from one address to another

transferOwner(address).notice: Transfer the onwer of contract to other user

transferTokenToOwner(uint256).notice: transfer Token balance to owner from account of contract

params._owner: address The address which owns the funds.
params._spender: address The address which will spend the funds.

params._owner: The address to query the the balance of.

balanceOf(address).return: An uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address.

allowance(address,address).notice: Function to check the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender.

approve(address,uint256).notice: Approve the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

balanceOf(address).notice: Gets the balance of the specified address.

balanceOfAvailable(address).notice: Gets available balance of the specified address

balanceOfFrozen(address).notice: Gets the frozen balance of the specified address

burn(uint256).notice: Destroy tokens Remove `_amount` tokens from the system irreversibly

burnFrom(address,uint256).notice: Destroy tokens from other account Remove `_amount` tokens from the system irreversibly on behalf of `_from`.

decreaseApproval(address,uint256).notice: Decrease the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To decrement allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

depositEtherToContract().notice: deposit ether to account of contract

freezeAccount(address,bool).notice: Frozen account of the specified address

freezeFunds(uint256).notice: Froze amount of money of the own address

freezeFundsFrom(address,bool,uint256).notice: Froze amount of money of the specified address

frozenAccount(address).notice: Gets frozen status of the specified address

increaseApproval(address,uint256).notice: Increase the amount of tokens that an owner allowed to a spender. approve should be called when allowed[_spender] == 0. To increment allowed value is better to use this function to avoid 2 calls (and wait until the first transaction is mined)

transfer(address,uint256).notice: Transfer token for a specified address

transferEtherToOwner(uint256).notice: transfer Ether balance to owner from account of contract

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).notice: Transfer tokens from one address to another

transferOwner(address).notice: Transfer the onwer of contract to other user

transferTokenToOwner(uint256).notice: transfer Token balance to owner from account of contract
